CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 19, 1960, pg. B2 reads:"National Leaders Preside - At the meeting of National Executive Committees of the Legion of Guardsman and Ladies Auxiliaries held at Webster Hall on Nov. 13, National Commander Charles R. Russell, above, of Marshalltown, La., presided over the man's session. National President Margaret F. Cobbs of Pittsburgh, presided over the women's session.  Mrs. Cobbs is the first Negro woman to hold such a high office in any veterans auxiliary.  The Legion of Guardsman stand for a strong and well-defended America, and is unalterably opposed to communism, and all foreignisms and idealogies [ideologies]. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Charles R. Russell and Margaret F. Cobbs wearing Legion of Guardsmen caps, standing in Smith Watkins Post Legion of Guardsmen for banquet
